TITLE:: SamplerPrepare
summary:: Internal per-voice preparation data for SuperSampler playback.
categories:: SuperSampler
related:: Classes/SamplerQuery, Classes/SSampler

DESCRIPTION::
Internal class. link::Classes/SamplerQuery:: builds one SamplerPrepare per voice when organizing a gesture: which sample and section to play, at what rate, from which position, when (wait time), with which envelope windows and normalization gain. They are stored on the gesture's link::Classes/SamplerArguments#-playSamples:: and consumed by the playback dispatch.

You normally never touch this class directly — control playback through link::Classes/SSampler#-key:: arguments instead.
